Description: We are the TubroTax of Cannabis
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Who is Taxnexus? Founded in Berkeley, California, Taxnexus is a financial technology service for the cannabis industry that solves real-world tax compliance problems for recreational and medical cannabis taxpayers and regulators. What Are We Doing? Taxnexus is the first global tax management software solution aimed to help cannabis industry participants (taxpayers) become and remain compliant with all state, county, and local jurisdictional cannabis excise and sales and use taxes. Cannabis POS and ERP software developers can adapt their existing, cloud-based offerings to Taxnexus API for cannabis businesses to calculate state, county and local excise taxes, track and store all tax data, and file monthly cannabis tax returns in an easy, inexpensive and compliant manner. Taxnexus API creates a financial chain of custody from the cannabis taxpayer to the state treasury. What is next? In 2018, Taxnexus will offer API-based tax calculation, transaction management and monthly tax return services. In the near future, Taxnexus will also provide remittance services to cannabis taxpayers.

Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: The intelligent workspace for coordinating team tasks Cohuman is for teams of any kind that need a simple and powerful way to coordinate the actions of their members. Unlike traditional collaboration solutions that are project or document-centric, Cohuman is people-centric. Yes, we share documents with each other and we collaborate on projects, but when it comes down to it, we are each responsible for our own specific set of tasks. Thatâ€™s what Cohuman is: a Task Network, where people create and share tasks. Each task is a container holding all the information you need: documents, followers, dates, dependencies and more. What makes Cohuman unique is that it organizes each task in a person or project list in order of priority. Lastly, intelligent permission settings allow team members to view shared task lists. Think of it as live status reports of everyone on your team and every project you work on. FOCUS - Tasks are prioritized so people can focus on doing the most important things first. FACETED TRANSPARENCY - Team members have visibility into each othersâ€™ Tasks. Sophisticated privacy controls determine what each person can see. INDIVIDUAL ACCOUNTABILITY - A Task can only have one owner, reducing business ambiguity while increasing accountability.  ACCESSIBILITY - Files, conversations and deadlines are centralized, secure and always accessible. EMAIL INTEGRATION - People can choose to receive and respond to Tasks via email without logging in to the web app. GOOGLE INTEGRATION - Share Google docs with greater ease; access your Google contacts; provide Cohuman to your team with Google Marketplace; View your Tasks on Google Calendar

Description: Prince William Sound Community College is a school in Valdez.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: The Prince William Sound Community College in Valdez, Alaska, is not simply a small college in a small town. It is a close-knit learning community that fosters inspiration, growth and learning. The school offers many opportunities for you to get involved on campus, whether through leadership activities, internships or campus events. Students may also join clubs like the Multicultural Club, Peer Advocates for Wellness or Sci-Fi Friday Club. If you’re seeking professional development, you can also partake in Student Government. If you want to journey to Anchorage to check out its shopping and cultural opportunities, it’s as easy as taking one of the daily flights or using public transportation. Two to three full-length theatre productions are hosted each year, as well as two sets of one-act plays from students in acting classes. A wellness center is also available to all students. Academics at the college include more than 25 undergraduate programs, from associate’s degrees to occupational certificates to baccalaureate transfer programs that are offered through partnerships with universities in the University of Alaska system. Some of the unique programs include Millwright, Oil Spill Response and Outdoor Leadership programs. Admissions are open, allowing any applicant above 18 years of age who has earned a high school diploma or GED to attend. The college welcomes students from all over the world with a flat tuition rate. Students who complete a FAFSA application may be eligible to receive financial aid through institutional scholarships and other forms of federal and state aid.

Full Description: Clock Session is an online time tracking and employee management software designed to help businesses and professionals efficiently track working hours, manage projects, and enhance productivity. This software offers a range of features to make time tracking and project management more streamlined and effective. Here are some of the key features and benefits of Clock Session: Automated Time Tracking: Clock Session allows employees to track their work hours effortlessly. It automates the time tracking process, reducing the need for manual entry and ensuring accurate records. Project Management: Users can create and manage projects, assign tasks, and track work progress within the software. This feature is especially valuable for businesses handling multiple projects simultaneously. Employee Management: Clock Session consolidates employee-related information into one integrated application. This simplifies workforce management, including attendance tracking and handling time-off requests. Efficient Resource Management: The software provides insights into how time is being utilized, helping businesses make informed decisions about resource allocation. Mobile Accessibility: Clock Session is accessible on various devices, including mobile phones, making it convenient for on-the-go time tracking. Data-Driven Decision-Making: With detailed time tracking and project management data, businesses can make data-driven decisions to improve efficiency and profitability. Clock Session is designed to meet the needs of freelancers, managers, and entire teams looking to enhance their time management and project tracking capabilities. It aims to make time tracking more efficient and flexible while promoting better productivity and resource management. Clock Session offers a range of benefits for businesses, freelancers, and professionals looking to enhance their time tracking, project management, and employee management processes. Here are some of the key benefits of using Clock Session: Efficient Time Tracking: Clock Session automates time tracking, making it easy for users to record their working hours accurately. This eliminates the need for manual entry, reducing errors and ensuring precise time records. Project Management: The software facilitates project creation and management, allowing users to assign tasks, monitor work progress, and keep projects on track. This feature is invaluable for businesses handling multiple projects simultaneously. Employee Management: Clock Session consolidates all employee-related information into one integrated platform. This simplifies attendance tracking, time-off requests, and employee management tasks, improving HR efficiency. Resource Allocation: With insights into how time is being spent on projects, businesses can make informed decisions about resource allocation. This can help optimize resource usage and enhance project profitability. Data-Driven Decision-Making: The software provides detailed time tracking and project management data, enabling businesses to make data-driven decisions. This data can be used to identify areas for improvement, boost efficiency, and increase productivity. Cost-Effective: By automating time tracking and reducing administrative overhead, Clock Session helps businesses save time and money. This cost-effective solution streamlines processes, improving the bottom line. Enhanced Productivity: With better time management and project tracking, Clock Session can boost overall productivity. It helps users focus on tasks, meet deadlines, and achieve project goals more efficiently.

Description: Rosen Systems, founded in 1917, is the country's premier industrial auction & appraisal company.
Headquarters Regions: Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex, Southern US
Full Description: The business was founded by the Rosen brothers, Gus and Ralph, in Cleveland in 1917. They became well-known throughout the midwest, attaining an enviable reputation for fair dealing. The company opened its Dallas office—now the headquarters—in 1947, under the direction of Irving Rosen, whose son, Michael Rosen, is the owner and president. If the auction sales are the most visible part of the business, then the appraisals of equipment, materials and real estate are an essential part of the business. There is a close relationship between the two specialties and it can be explained simply: being an appraiser makes us better auctioneers and being auctioneers makes us better appraisers. Their business is nationwide and beyond. In a typical year, their appraisers and auctioneers will travel through much of the U.S., with occasional missions to Canada and Mexico, as well as in Europe.
